=== TASK ===
# Seller Dashboard

## Overview
Create a role-specific Seller Dashboard for ProBid that enables sellers to manage their listings and related activities end-to-end. The page surfaces active listings, draft intake flows, upcoming auctions, inspection requests, and recent sales, and tightly integrates with a robust File Upload & Storage Management system for listing photos (15–25 images per listing) with image processing, CDN hosting, and secured access controls. The solution must be built with a reuse-first approach, be highly responsive, real-time where needed, and adhere to strict runtime safety rules for all API/data handling.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Seller Dashboard is a role-specific cockpit for sellers to efficiently manage their inventory, intake workflows, ongoing auctions, inspection coordination, and sales activity. It provides quick actions, status visibility, and centralized access to ancillary operations (uploads, approvals, and communications).

Goals:
- Empower sellers to:
  - Create and monitor active listings with 15–25 uploaded listing photos.
  - Initiate and track draft intake flows with AI-assisted enrichment and validation.
  - Review upcoming auctions and set reserve/pricing parameters.
  - Manage inspection requests (scheduling, status, results, and documentation).
  - View and analyze recent sales, including key metrics (counts, average sale price, sell-through rate).
  - Access notifications, messages, and ops tasks related to their listings.
- Ensure secure, scalable, and fast experiences with real-time updates where appropriate (bids, inspection status, and approvals), with robust access controls and auditability.

Connected features:
- File Upload & Storage Management: Robust photo uploads (15–25 images per listing) with image processing (validation, resizing, thumbnails), CDN hosting, and secured access controls.
- Real-time updates: Bids, inspection results, and ops statuses via Supabase Realtime or WebSockets.
- AI-enabled intake enrichment: Multi-step intake flow with external data enrichment (ID/serial/VIN-like identifiers) and AI vision QA pipeline (provider-agnostic, pluggable).
- Auctions: Upcoming auctions view with status, scheduling, and quick actions; proxy bidding considerations, anti-sniping, and reserve logic.
- Admin/Ops workflow:RBAC and gated access for the seller-facing actions, with audit trails.
- Analytics: Key metrics around listings, sell-through, and average sale price.

Visual guidance:
- A clean, responsive, data-rich dashboard with clear visual hierarchy, strong actions, and consistent branding aligned to the provided color and typography system. Cards, lists, and charts emphasize status, progress, and outcomes. Real-time indicators use neon yellow-green for active/highlights, while errors use red.

## Components to Build
- SellerDashboardShell
  - Layout: Left sidebar navigation (Listings, Auctions, Inspections, Sales, Settings, Support) and main content area with top action bar.
  - Persistence: Bottom navigation on mobile; persistent top nav on desktop.
- ListingsPanel
  - ListingCard component with status badge (Draft, Pending Review, Approved, In Auction, Sold), quick actions (Edit, View, Cancel), thumbnail gallery, and key metrics.
  - CreateListingCTA to start intake wizard.
- DraftIntakeFlow
  - Multi-step wizard UI collecting: identifier (ID/serial/VIN), photos (15–25), basic specs, condition notes, AI enrichment results, and validation statuses.
  - Inline AI QA results panel with tags, confidence, and hard-fail vs warning indicators.
- ActiveAuctionsPanel
  - Upcoming auctions list with schedule, reserve price, current high bid, and quick actions.
  - Auction heat map or progress bars for time-to-close.
- InspectionRequestsPanel
  - List of inspection requests with status (Scheduled, In Progress, Completed), assigned inspector, dates, and action buttons to reschedule or add notes.
- RecentSalesPanel
  - List with big numeric stats (total sales, avg sale price, top-selling items) and mini-graphs/bar charts.
- ActivityFeedPanel
  - Stream of events (inspections scheduled, bids received, wins) with timestamps and actor.
- MetricsPanel
  - KPIs: listing count, sell-through rate, average sale price, inspection turnaround, and notification counts.
- UploadManager
  - Photo uploader supporting 15–25 images per listing, with drag-and-drop, progress bars, per-image validation, and retry/fallback handling.
  - Image processing: thumbnail creation, auto-orientation, compression presets, and CDN-uploaded URL generation.
- AIEnrichmentPanel
  - Display enrichment results, structured JSON evidence, warnings, and actions (accept enrichment, flag for review).
- NotificationsPanel
  - In-app notifications with read/unread state and actionable items.
- DataViz
  - Minimalist horizontal bar charts and simple KPI visuals using neon yellow-green accents.
- API Integration Adapters
  - Enrichment API adapter (external data providers).
  - Vision QA adapter (provider-agnostic, pluggable).
- Auth & RBAC Guards
  - Seller role guards for all restricted actions; audit trail of sensitive actions.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks/Tech:
  - Next.js with App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.
  - Use SWR or React Query for data fetching with caching and optimistic updates.
  - Supabase client for data operations and storage with edge functions where appropriate.
- UI/UX:
  - Adhere to the design system: color palette, typography, spacing, and layout guidelines described in Visual Style.
  - Components must be accessible (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, focus styles).
  - Always guard against null/undefined values when dealing with arrays; use data ?? [] patterns.
- State management:
  - Global UI state for notifications, global loading, and active tab; local component state for forms and modals.
  - Initialize useState with appropriate types, e.g., useState<Sale[]>([]), useState<Listing[]>([]).
- File Upload & Storage:
  - Implement UploadManager with:
    - Accept multiple images per listing (15–25).
    - Client-side validation (types, size limits, aspect ratios if required).
    - Progress indicators and retry logic.
    - After upload, call API to initiate server-side image processing (resize, orientation) and store in CDN-backed hosting.
    - Ensure signed/secured access tokens for image URLs; avoid exposing raw storage links publicly.
  - Ensure all image URLs are stored in listing records reliably and with proper null-safety: (photos ?? []).map(...) guarded, etc.
- AI Enrichment:
  - Integrate pluggable enrichment flow: a multi-step intake with external APIs; results stored as structured JSON in listing.enrichment.
  - Validation: hard fails vs warnings with confidence scores; present results in UI with actions.
- Real-time updates:
  - For auctions and bids, use Supabase Realtime or WebSockets; gracefully handle offline/latency with optimistic UI toggles and reconciliation.
- Validation & Error handling:
  - All inputs validated on client and server; provide user-friendly error messages.
  - Always use null-safe access patterns for API responses and database results.

### Backend
- API Endpoints (Next.js API Routes / Edge Functions):
  - POST /api/listings: create a listing with initial draft data; returns listingId and status.
  - GET /api/listings?status=...: fetch filtered lists; ensure response shape is validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - PUT /api/listings/:id: update listing fields (title, description, pricing, status).
  - POST /api/listings/:id/photos: upload photo metadata results; handle image processing orchestrations.
  - POST /api/intake/start: begin draft intake flow; initialize AI enrichment.
  - POST /api/intake/:step: progress intake steps; store step results.
  - GET /api/intake/:id/enrichment: fetch enrichment results; parse as structured JSON.
  - POST /api/auctions: create upcoming auction with schedule and reserve logic.
  - GET /api/auctions?listingId=...: fetch upcoming auctions for a listing.
  - POST /api/inspections: create inspection request, schedule, and update.
  - GET /api/sales/recent: fetch recent sales for the seller.
  - GET /api/notifications: fetch in-app notifications.
  - POST /api/storage/upload: (optional) server-assisted upload token generation.
  - Supabase usage:
    - Use Postgres tables with RLS for listings, photos, intakes, auctions, inspections, sales, and notifications.
    - Use edge functions for heavy lifting and data enrichment orchestration.
- Database Tables (Schema highlights):
  - sellers(id, name, email, etc.)
  - listings(id, seller_id, title, description, status, created_at, updated_at)
  - listing_photos(id, listing_id, url, order, width, height, stored_at)
  - intakes(id, listing_id, current_step, status, results_json, enriched_at)
  - enrich_results(id, listing_id, provider, data_json, confidence, hard_fail, warnings)
  - auctions(id, listing_id, start_time, end_time, reserve_price, current_bid, status)
  - bids(id, auction_id, bidder_id, amount, placed_at)
  - inspections(id, listing_id, scheduled_at, inspector_id, status, notes)
  - sales(id, listing_id, sale_price, sold_at, buyer_id)
  - notifications(id, seller_id, type, message, read, created_at)
  - audit_logs(id, actor_id, action, target_type, target_id, timestamp)
- Security:
  - Implement Row Level Security (RLS) for all sensitive data; ensure sellers can only access their own listings and related data.
  - Use signed URLs for image access; CDN hosting with restricted tokens.
  - Webhooks for Stripe payments must be idempotent and auditable.
- Validation:
  - Validate input payloads at API boundaries; sanitize inputs to prevent injection; ensure optional fields default safely.
  - Always guard array operations on results (data ?? []) as per runtime safety rules.

### Integration
- How components connect:
  - SellerDashboardShell fetches data via /api/listings, /api/auctions, /api/inspections, /api/sales/recent, and /api/notifications.
  - ListingsPanel renders ListingCard items built from /api/listings data; each card has actions that call /api/listings/:id, /api/listings/:id/photos, etc.
  - UploadManager handles client-side uploads and then calls /api/listings/:id/photos to persist references; image processing happens via backend (Edge Functions) and CDN storage.
  - DraftIntakeFlow drives the multi-step intake; it calls /api/intake/start and /api/intake/:step to progress; enrichment results are fetched from /api/intake/:id/enrichment.
  - ActiveAuctionsPanel consumes /api/auctions for upcoming auctions; bids and real-time updates push via Supabase Realtime.
  - InspectionRequestsPanel uses /api/inspections to create/schedule and update statuses; updates reflect in ActivityFeedPanel.
  - RecentSalesPanel uses /api/sales/recent to display patterns, with DataViz components rendering charts from the data.
  - AIEnrichmentPanel displays structured results from /api/intake/:id/enrichment with options to accept or flag.
  - NotificationsPanel consumes /api/notifications and triggers in-app messages for important events.
- Data flow safety:
  - Always ensure arrays use guards: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - When handling API responses, validate shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Use consistent default values: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.
  - Access nested API data with optional chaining: obj?.property?.nested.
  - Initialize all React state for arrays: useState<Listing[]>([]), useState<Photo[]>([]), etc.

## User Experience Flow
1) Seller lands on Dashboard
   - Sees top metrics: total listings, sell-through rate, average sale price.
   - Quick actions: Create Listing, View Active Listings, Open Draft Intake.
   - Left navigation: Listings, Auctions, Inspections, Sales, Settings, Support.
2) Create Listing (Draft Intake)
   - Click Create Listing CTA to start Intake Wizard.
   - Step 1: Enter identifier (ID/serial/VIN-like) and auto-enrichment fetch.
   - Step 2: Upload 15–25 photos with drag-and-drop; progress bars for each image; client-side validation (format/size).
   - Step 3: Validate basic specs; AI Vision QA runs in background; show results with hard/fail and warnings.
   - Step 4: Confirm details and submit for internal review; status updates to Draft -> Pending Review.
3) Active Listings & Management
   - Cards show status badges (Draft, Pending Review, Approved, In Auction, Sold).
   - Actions: Edit, View, Cancel; quick navigation to related auctions or inspections.
   - Click View to open a detailed listing page with photo gallery, bidding info (if in auction), and inspection schedule.
4) Upcoming Auctions
   - View listings with upcoming auction windows; edit reserve price, schedule, and monitor current bid state.
   - Real-time bid updates appear as they occur.
5) Inspection Requests
   - Inspectors scheduled; view status; reschedule or attach notes/documents.
6) Recent Sales
   - Review recent sales performance; metrics and lightweight charts update live.
7) Notifications & Activity
   - In-app notifications appear; action items flagged; activity feed streams events like inspections scheduled, bids received, and wins.
8) File Upload & Storage
   - Uploads are validated client-side; server-side processing ensures orientation, compression, thumbnails; CDN-hosted assets served with secure URLs; photo data stored in listing_photos table.

